# SECURITY CONFIGURATION FOR STREAMING APPLICATION
# 
# This configuration balances security with functionality for a streaming app that:
# - Embeds external video players (VidSrc, VidLink, AutoEmbed, etc.)
# - Loads TMDB images without CORP headers
# - Uses React with styled-components requiring inline styles
# 
# Security Trade-offs Explained:
# - COEP: unsafe-none (allows TMDB images, required for functionality)
# - CORP: cross-origin (enables external image loading)
# - CSP: unsafe-inline (required for React/styled-components)
# - Removed X-XSS-Protection (redundant with CSP)

